  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You extend a finger towards one creature you can see, sending a jet of divine fire roaring towards it. Make a <strong>ranged spell attack</strong>, dealing <strong>8d6 radiant damage</strong> on a hit and causing the target to catch fire for the duration of the spell. On a miss, the spell ends.</p><p>At the end of each of its turns, the target must make a <strong>Dexterity saving throw</strong>, taking 2d6 damage on a failed save and ending the spell on a successful one. If the target is reduced to 0 hit points, the spell ends.</p><p>As a bonus action while the spell lasts, you can cause one creature of your choice within 5 feet of the target to regain 2d6 hit points.</p>",
